<br>
Either way, there will always be loot greedy people on CoG raids. And there will always be people there for other reasons.  The support group in my eyes isn't that different from the rest of the team, and using &quot;amount of work&quot; or whether they can be in the same room with Lady Vox or not to try to distinguish them from the rest just doesn't make a lot of sense to me... there are plenty of people who are 52 and less who don't put in as much as some others, but that shouldn't exclude them from the roll either.  Point is, noone should be excluded if they are present for the entire raid. <br>
<br>
That being said, I think Steelheart or any of the organizers who have shown over and over that they are here to truly support the raids should have a right to decide how many people they want in a support team. Or the raid leader. Similarly, it's also their decision as to whether the support team should roll or not.  Leave it up to every individual to decide if they agree enough to want to participate or not. <p><HR>
